Background Species: Poecile carolinensis -- Carolina Chickadee; Cardinalis cardinalis -- Northern Cardinal
Media notes: Scolding at a Red-bellied Woodpecker near a nest hole

A microphone with furry cover placed in the bird garden caused alarm for several species.  This short note, clearly thrush-like is not in the Library of Natural Sounds to the best of my knowledge.  This is the male of a pair nesting about 20m away. I suspect it is an alarm note given the reaction of other feeder birds.  This pair and others often feed on a tube of meal worms.
